(3/22/02 4:01:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14992.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sick about Death Touch..</span><hr size=1> Ring around the Collar encounters get rid of the main tank, and some stuff like Grieg certainly doesen't call for main tanking - almost all of the damage he is dishing out is from AE's.<br><br>But any mob that melees for a bajillion damage and takes half a year to kill can only be killed in one of two ways 1) main tank - and I don't mean &quot;CH rotation main tank&quot;, I just mean the clerics focus their heals on the warrior that happens to have aggro at the time.  And 2) zerg the shit out of the mob.  As people die, res them back in, or stand on the corpse for better leverage if your Zerg is truely a swarm to admire.  Keep up such a sustained amount of damage that the mob runs out of hitpoints before you run out of players.<br><br>Most luclin fights last so long they wind up being a combination of the two.  <br><br>Oh yeah, and death touch sucks shit, and never should have been on any mob whose title didn't include &quot;deity&quot;<br><br>DT was a tool to make a 32k hitpoint mob able to actually kill a few people before it croaked.  It has no buisness in a drawn out fight.<br><br>But I've been over all this ;p  <p><font size="2"><b>Kreugen, Cavalier of Brell</b></font><br><font size ="2"><i>Fires of Heaven Officer</i></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uradiatevaliantbeard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Radiate Valiantbeard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 137<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 5:53:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14992.topic&index